## Q6 — Deadlock Handling (Deadlock Detection Algorithm)

### What is being asked?
3 student groups (processes) share 2 resource types (projectors, USB hubs). Some resources are allocated. Check if there is a **deadlock** using the resource allocation graph / detection algorithm.

### Difference from Banker's Algorithm:
- **Banker's** = Prevention (check before granting request)
- **Detection** = Find if deadlock already exists right now

### How Detection Works:
Similar logic to safety algorithm:
- `Work = Available`
- Find any process whose `Request ≤ Work` (it can complete with available resources)
- Simulate it finishing → add its allocation back to Work
- If some processes can NEVER finish → they are in deadlock

---

### FILE: `deadlock_detect.c`

```c
#include <stdio.h>

#define P 3   // Number of processes (student groups)
#define R 2   // Number of resource types (projectors, USB hubs)

int main() {
    // What each process currently holds
    int allocation[P][R] = {
        {1, 0},   // P0 holds 1 projector, 0 USB hubs
        {2, 1},   // P1 holds 2 projectors, 1 USB hub
        {0, 2}    // P2 holds 0 projectors, 2 USB hubs
    };

    // What each process is currently requesting (still needs)
    int request[P][R] = {
        {0, 0},   // P0 requests nothing — it's done or waiting for nothing
        {2, 0},   // P1 is requesting 2 more projectors
        {0, 1}    // P2 is requesting 1 more USB hub
    };

    // Currently available resources
    int available[R] = {0, 1};  // 0 projectors free, 1 USB hub free

    int finish[P];
    int work[R];
    int deadlocked[P];
    int deadlock_count = 0;

    // Initialize: mark all processes as unfinished
    for (int i = 0; i < P; i++) finish[i] = 0;
    for (int j = 0; j < R; j++) work[j] = available[j];

    printf("Deadlock Detection Algorithm\n");
    printf("============================\n");
    printf("Available: Projectors=%d, USB hubs=%d\n\n", available[0], available[1]);

    // Run detection
    int found = 1;
    while (found) {
        found = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < P; i++) {
            if (finish[i] == 0) {
                // Can this process complete with current work?
                int can_finish = 1;
                for (int j = 0; j < R; j++) {
                    if (request[i][j] > work[j]) {
                        can_finish = 0;
                        break;
                    }
                }

                if (can_finish) {
                    // Simulate process finishing — release its resources
                    printf("P%d can finish. Releasing its resources.\n", i);
                    for (int j = 0; j < R; j++)
                        work[j] += allocation[i][j];
                    finish[i] = 1;
                    found = 1;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    // Check who couldn't finish
    printf("\nResult:\n");
    for (int i = 0; i < P; i++) {
        if (finish[i] == 0) {
            deadlocked[deadlock_count++] = i;
        }
    }

    if (deadlock_count == 0) {
        printf("No deadlock detected. All processes can complete.\n");
    } else {
        printf("DEADLOCK DETECTED!\n");
        printf("Processes in deadlock: ");
        for (int i = 0; i < deadlock_count; i++)
            printf("P%d ", deadlocked[i]);
        printf("\n");
    }

    return 0;
}
```

---

### Manual Trace:
- Work = [0, 1]
- P0 requests [0,0]: 0≤0, 0≤1 → YES, can finish. Work = [0,1] + [1,0] = [1,1]
- P1 requests [2,0]: 2≤1? → NO, cannot finish yet
- P2 requests [0,1]: 0≤1, 1≤1 → YES, can finish. Work = [1,1] + [0,2] = [1,3]
- Now check P1 again: requests [2,0]: 2≤1? → Still NO
- P1 is stuck → **P1 is in deadlock**

---

### Compile and Run:
```bash
gcc deadlock_detect.c -o deadlock_detect
./deadlock_detect
```

### Output:
```
Deadlock Detection Algorithm
============================
Available: Projectors=0, USB hubs=1

P0 can finish. Releasing its resources.
P2 can finish. Releasing its resources.

Result:
DEADLOCK DETECTED!
Processes in deadlock: P1
```

