## Q9 — Disk Scheduling (SCAN / Elevator Algorithm)

### What is being asked?
Disk requests: `176, 79, 34, 60, 92, 11, 41, 114`. Head starts at **50**, moving toward **higher tracks**. Use SCAN algorithm. Calculate total head movement. Also compare with FCFS.

### What is SCAN?
SCAN works like an elevator:
1. Move in one direction (toward higher tracks), servicing all requests on the way
2. When you reach the end (or last request), **reverse direction**
3. Service remaining requests on the way back

---

### FILE: `scan.c`

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int compare(const void* a, const void* b) {
    return (*(int*)a - *(int*)b);
}

int main() {
    int requests[] = {176, 79, 34, 60, 92, 11, 41, 114};
    int n = 8;
    int head = 50;
    int direction = 1;   // 1 = moving toward higher tracks

    // Sort requests
    int sorted[8];
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) sorted[i] = requests[i];
    qsort(sorted, n, sizeof(int), compare);

    printf("SCAN (Elevator) Disk Scheduling\n");
    printf("Initial head position: %d, moving toward higher tracks\n\n");
    printf("Sorted requests: ");
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) printf("%d ", sorted[i]);
    printf("\n\n");

    int total_movement = 0;
    int current = head;
    int service_order[20];
    int order_count = 0;

    // Find where head is in the sorted array
    // Split into: requests >= head (go right first) and requests < head (go left after)

    // PHASE 1: Move right (service all tracks >= head)
    printf("Phase 1: Moving RIGHT (higher tracks)\n");
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        if (sorted[i] >= head) {
            int dist = sorted[i] - current;
            printf("  Head moves from %d to %d (distance = %d)\n",
                   current, sorted[i], dist);
            total_movement += dist;
            service_order[order_count++] = sorted[i];
            current = sorted[i];
        }
    }

    // PHASE 2: Reverse direction, move left (service tracks < head)
    printf("\nPhase 2: Reversing direction, moving LEFT (lower tracks)\n");
    for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        if (sorted[i] < head) {
            int dist = current - sorted[i];
            printf("  Head moves from %d to %d (distance = %d)\n",
                   current, sorted[i], dist);
            total_movement += dist;
            service_order[order_count++] = sorted[i];
            current = sorted[i];
        }
    }

    printf("\nService Order: ");
    for (int i = 0; i < order_count; i++) printf("%d ", service_order[i]);

    printf("\nTotal Head Movement (SCAN) = %d\n\n", total_movement);

    // ---- Compare with FCFS ----
    printf("For comparison — FCFS Head Movement:\n");
    current = head;
    int fcfs_movement = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        fcfs_movement += abs(requests[i] - current);
        printf("  Head: %d → %d (dist=%d)\n", current, requests[i], abs(requests[i]-current));
        current = requests[i];
    }
    printf("Total Head Movement (FCFS) = %d\n", fcfs_movement);
    printf("\nSCAN is more efficient than FCFS in this case.\n");

    return 0;
}
```

